nsient emission. High resolution imaging can be used to\nconstrain the location of the disk and help to discriminate between different\nmodels of disk emission. For some small disks, interferometry is needed to\nresolve the disk location.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Apr 2008 11:23:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
