 collisional excitation by shock wave from a common\nexciting source is unlikely. Instead, the synchronized time variation of the\nmasers can be explained if all the maser features are excited by infrared\nradiation from dust which is heated by a common exciting source with a rapid\nvariability.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Apr 2008 14:27:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
